    public class HairDryerStateSILModel
extends fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.models.AtomicModel
    The class HairDryerStateSILModel defines a simulation model tracking the state changes on a hair dryer.

    Description

    The model emits events towards another model simulating the electricity consumption of the hair dryer given its current operating state (switched on/off, high/low power mode).

    Invariant

     invariant      true

    Created on : 2020-12-16

    Author:
    Jacques Malenfant
